title: Legend of Stanky Creek TT and XC
CRMC Road Race & TN State Crit Championships
MOAB Mousetail Challenge TT & XC Races
2012 Monkey Bell Classic / Tennessee MTB State Cha
description:
2012 Monkey Bell Classic Tennessee MTB State Championship Presented by Biker\'s Choice and Trace Bikes.  
Time Trial and Cross Country MTN Bike Races
Saturday August 11th and Sunday August 12th, 2012
Montgomery Bell State Park
Dickson, TN
course:
Come enjoy some great Middle Tennessee Singletrack at beautiful Montgomery Bell State Park. Race your friends and foes head to head on the Time Trial on Saturday and then
again on the XC course on Sunday. The XC course is approx. 9 miles with a mixture of fast flowing singletack, tight twisting singletrack and a few challenging sections thrown in
for good measure. New start this year to try to thin out the groups before getting into the tight singletrack. Post Race Meal Provided after races on Sunday.

Time Trial: Cat 1’s begin at 3:00 pm Sat 8/11 followed by Cat 2 and Cat 3. Cash prizes to Cat 1 & 2, Medals to Cat 3 and Juniors
Never raced a TT before? Everyone starts separately at 1 minute intervals & will be riding the 3.1 mile RED trail the fastest trail at
Montgomery Bell. Pre-ride Saturday until 2:30pm. Trail will reopen after the time trail
registration: Online Registration available through your USACycling account.  On-Site Registration Opens Sat. @ 1:00pm for the TT and XC and again at 7:00am Sun morning.
notes:
Monkey Bell Classic is a USA Cycling Sanctioned Event.  All USA Cycling MTB rules apply.
USAC license is required for all Pro\'s and Cat 1\'s / One Day licenses are available for $5.  Annual licenses will also be available.

Monkey Bell will host the MTB State Championship XC race for 2012 therefore this will be a division 1 event with double the TBRA points of a normal MTB race.  

District Medals and Championship Jerseys will be awarded on the day of the event.  District medals run 3 deep and a Championship jersey is awarded to the winner in each TBRA category for the XC race only.  Cat 3 racers will not receive a jersey but will receive district medals.
directions:
Start/Finish ADDRESS: 830 Bill Duke Road, White Bluff, TN 37187.  Montgomery Bell State Park has an Inn, Cabins, and camping onsite.  Hotels are available not to far away in Dickson, TN.
http://www.tn.gov/environment/parks/MontgomeryBell/

title: Memphis Invitational Club Championship - Time Tria
MSG Cyclo-cross Series  3&4 p/b The Town of Unicoi
840 Fondo Festival
description:
TN 840 is opening to bicycles before the first car gets to drive on it. Don\'t miss this historic one day event.

Why come to the event?

• To celebrate the completion of State Route 840 with Governor Bill Haslam and TDOT Commissioner John Schroer.
• To honor the contractors who built it and the communities it serves.
• To announce the combined State of Tennessee and I am the Engine message of connecting eating healthy and active lifestyles with a happier community.


What you (participant) get:
• A fully timed course with a King of the Mountain timed section.
• Be the first in history to ride fresh asphalt on a new state route legally closed for cyclist only!
• Celebration of the completion of 840 with the Governor of Tennessee and state officials, contractors, communities and friends.
• Fully staffed and stocked rest stops with amazing food and provided by Whole Foods Market.
• A 840 Fondo Festival gift bag.
• Commemorative t-shirt
• A hot shower (or two or three) after your ride
• A lovingly crafted post-ride meal from any one of our multiple local food vendors.
• The exceptional post-ride FondoFest with music and great entertainment in Historic Leipers Fork.
course:
3 challenging routes. 

The 100 mile Gran route takes riders from Leipers fork out to TN-840 where it departs for some of the most scenic (and hilly) terrain in Middle Tennessee. King of the Mountain timed climb up one of the best climbs in the area. 

65 mile Medio route follows the longer route, but cuts out some of the challenge and a lot of the climbing

35 mile Piccolo route rides out to the 840 route and makes it\'s way back to the party in Leipers Fork via the small community of Greenbriar.

Also, there is a FREE family ride that goes along 840.
notes: Though a Gran Fondo isn\'t a race, it can be competitive. Whether you want to enjoy the scenery, the challenging route, and the great food, or set a personal best up some of our most notorious climbs, you are bound to have a great time.
directions:
Historic Leipers Fork, Tennessee • Old Hillsboro Rd. serves as the Gran, Medio and Piccolo Start and Finish. 

South of Franklin, TN on Old Hillsboro Rd. Take Hwy 96 West out of downtown Franklin to Old Hillsboro Rd and take a left. You can\'t miss it.

Country Boy Cyclocross Race

address.street: Holder Rd and North Chapel Rd

description: Harpeth Bicycles Racing presents the Country Boy Cyclocross Race. A fast, afternoon of racing on a truly local course. Legs tired from the 840 Fondo? Come out and spectate. Feeling frisky? Come out and race.
course: A fast course incorporating the best features of the terrain, and some that we added for good measure. Mostly hay fields, with some dirt, and maybe a few surprises.
registration:
Online registration via USA Cycling
Day of registration at the event (add $5 to race fee for day of registration)
directions:
From Nashville: Take I-65 South to Hwy 96 and head East to North Chapel Rd. Take a right on North Chapel and follow it to Holder Rd (dead end). Race signs will show you to parking. 

(If you ride the Tuesday night HBC ride, you go past this farm every week)
